NEW YORK MARINE COMPANY, as Owner of THE Steam Tug DIXIE, Libelant-Appellant, v. THE Steam Tug NEWARK, Her Engines, etc., The Delaware, Lackawanna & Western Railroad Company, Claimant-Appellant. No. 226. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 5, 1934. John E. Morrissey, of New York City, for appellant. Burlingham, "Feeder, Fearey, Clark & Hupper, of Now York City (Chauneey I. Clark and Stanley R. Wright, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.
